title: The Time Travelers
description_full: In 1964, a team of scientists is trying to develop a view screen into the future. What they in fact get is a portal and they soon find themselves on the other side, 107 years into the future in the year 2071, when the portal collapses. The Earth of the future is barren and they are soon attacked by mutated humans but rescued by a group of scientists who are building a spaceship to take them to a new planet. They learn that much of Earth was destroyed as the result of a nuclear war. When it's determined that the visitors from the past cannot be included in the planned voyage, they work furiously to rebuild the portal and return to their own time before departure day. Meanwhile, always under the threat of attack from the mutants , friendships are formed and they learn of life in the future including the use of robots for menial tasks.â€”garykmcd

title: Comes a Bright Day
description_full: A romantic thriller set during the armed robbery of one of London's most exclusive jewelers.

title: The Art of War II: Betrayal
title_english: The Art of War II: Betrayal
title_long: The Art of War II: Betrayal (2008)
description_full: When Agent Neil Shaw comes out of hiding to vindicate his former mentor's murder, he winds up on the trail of betrayal and lethal corruption. Under the charge of his friend and a senatorial candidate, his mission is to set things straight. But when more people turn up dead, Shaw realizes that he's been set up as bait.â€”Anonymous

title: Andie the Great
description_full: After dropping out of University and moving back in with her parents, Andie tries to figure out her place in the world.

title: Three Cockeyed Sailors
description_full: Three British sailors find they've accidentally strayed on board a German warship during World War II. They then proceed to take it over and requisition it for the Royal Navy.

title: Get Better: A Film About Frank Turner
title_english: Get Better: A Film About Frank Turner
title_long: Get Better: A Film About Frank Turner (2016)
description_full: "Get Better: A Film About Frank Turner" is a yearlong character study of one of the hardest working musicians on earth. Encompassing footage from friends, family and fans across England, Europe and the USA, film maker and friend Ben Morse set out to capture a band who are constantly in motion, only to find that they suddenly stopped. Forced to pause for the first time in ten years, 'Get Better: A Film About Frank Turner' explores what drives a man to stay on the road, and what that means for his life and those around him. In candid interviews, Frank, the band and everyone they meet explore what drives someone ever onwards.

title: Sibel
description_full: 25-year-old Sibel lives with her father and sister in a secluded village in the mountains of Turkey's Black Sea region. Sibel is a mute, but she communicates by using the ancestral whistled language of the area. There she crosses path with a fugitive. Injured, threatening and vulnerable, he is the first one to take a fresh look at her.

title: Samurai Rauni
description_full: Villagers are afraid of Samurai Rauni Reposaarelainen, who keeps them on their toes every day. When someone places a bounty on Rauni's head, he goes after this mysterious person.

title: The Silent Forest
description_full: Hearing-impaired teenager Chang Cheng transfers to a school for children with special needs. However, the world of the hearing-impaired doesn't seem quiet at all. When Chang witnesses the "game" taking place in the last row on the school bus, his excitement about blending into a new environment immediately turns into fear. Seeing Bei Bei, the girl he has a crush on, getting hurt so badly, Xiao Guang, the ringleader, behaving like a king and other schoolmates acting innocent, Chang debates with himself on whether he should reveal the cruel truth about the game or whether he should join in. As the divide between the perpetrators and the victim begins to blur, confusion and anxiety grow among everyone in school.

title: Jumbo
description_full: Jeanne (Portrait of a Lady on Fire's Noemie Merlant), a shy young woman, works as a night watchwoman in an amusement park and lives at home with her elderly mother. Her mother is desperate for her to meet a man, but Jeanne prefers to spend her time with the park's newest attraction - Jumbo, the tilt-a-whirl ride.

title: Lyle
description_full: A mother's grief over the death of her toddler leads to horror.

title: This Lady Called Life
description_full: Abandoned by her family, young single mother Aiye struggles to survive but stays focused on her dream of becoming an elite chef.

title: Welcome to Death Row
description_full: The true story of the rise and fall of Death Row Records.

title: American Fable
description_full: When 11-year-old Gitty discovers that her beloved father is hiding a wealthy man in her family's silo in order to save their struggling farm, she is forced to choose between saving the man's life or protecting her family from the consequences of their actions. AMERICAN FABLE is a fairytale thriller set in the 1980s rural Midwest about a courageous girl living in a dark - sometimes magical - world.

title: True Mothers
description_full: It is not strange or unusual for a couple to want to procreate and have a child. However, things are not proceeding smoothly for the couple formed by Kiyokazu and his wife Satoko. Despite steadily trying to get the wife pregnant the couple yield to reality and, exhorted by a professional association, the couple proceed to adopt a boy. They two are happily adapting to their adopted son, but a woman named Hikari Katakura shows up soon enough emphasizing she is the boy's biological mother. Satoko decides to face Hikari.â€”aghaemi

title: I Really Hate My Job
description_full: 'Every day is another day closer to the day I'll never have to do this again.' Five women, one restaurant, one night, one birthday, one breakdown. Then the phone rings. A famous actor is coming for dinner. I Really Hate My Job is the story of an evening in a cafÃ© in London's Soho. As in so many jobs, nothing much happens - except laughter, song, rage, collapse, intrigue, cooking, lying, nudity, conversation, secrets, love, friendship, ageing, hatred, rat-infestation and the arrival of a movie star. I Really Hate My Job. Who hasn't said it? A career. It's what happens when you lose control of a car on a wet road and it slams into a brick wall. You might assume they're just three waitresses, one cook and one dishwasher but they see themselves as an artist, an actor, a lover, an author and a philosopher.â€”Anonymous

title: An American Hate Crime
description_full: Jake (Daniel Byrne) a college drop out along with his friends decide to take their homophobia to a whole other level when when they decide to download a gay oriented social media app where they would lure and attack innocent victims. Noah ( Dylan Hartman). a just coming to terms gay teen doesn't know who to talk to about his feelings and turns to the same social media app the attackers use on their prey. Told from both perspectives of the main characters and a chilling conclusion that will alter everyone's lives forever.

title: The Dark Side of the Moon
title_english: The Dark Side of the Moon
title_long: The Dark Side of the Moon (1990)
description_full: It is the year 2022. A mysterious systems failure causes the crew of a spaceship to be stranded on the dark side of the moon, while rapidly running out of fuel and oxygen. They are surprised to discover a NASA space shuttle floating in space, and board it in the hope of salvaging some supplies. One by one, the crew is possessed and killed, and it is up to Paxton Warner to find the links between the dark side of the moon, the Bermuda Triangle, and the Devil himself.â€”Film Classics

title: Conni and the Cat
description_full: For the very first time, Conni goes on a big trip without her family. Of course her best friends Anna and Simon are joining, but unfortunately she is not allowed to take Cat Mau with her. As they arrived in the hostel, an old mill close to a castle, Conni discovers that Mau had come as a blind passenger. Secretly she cheers, although she knows that animals are forbidden in the castle and the hostess, Ms. Weingartner, is allergic to cats. Conni tries to hide Mau, but the cheeky cat cares little. He explores the surroundings curiously and does a lot of nonsense. Ms. Weingartner identifies her son's pet, the sweet raccoon Oskar, as the culprit and wants to take him to the zoo. And then things disappear from the hostel in a strange way. Conni and her friends have to act quickly: Will the children be able to save raccoon Oskar, tame Mau and also find a real thief?â€”youngfilms

title: No Way Out
description_full: A mob hitman wants to retire, but his bosses don't think that's a good idea. Complications and many bloody shootouts ensue.

title: Red Ribbon Blues
description_full: After attending his 23rd funeral for a friend with AIDS, Troy and his friends hatch a plan to steal the HIV drugs that they need. One successful heist leads to another and another until they have so much inventory they decide to begin their own community distribution program.â€”Havan_IronOak@Bigfoot.com

title: Acid Horizon
description_full: Acid Horizon closely follows a deep sea explorer trying to save the planet. Dr. Erik Cordes is searching for a "Supercoral" that will survive Ocean Acidification and help prevent future extinctions. Is he too late?

title: Nightwing
description_full: A colony of vampire bats terrorize a small Indian community in New Mexico. Standard "Nature goes berserk" plot takes a twist toward the end when supernatural forces are discovered working through the bats.â€”B.M.

title: In Between
description_full: A young punk rocker in Istanbul tracks down a cruise ticket to California on the night of his birthday gig. Based on the director's personal family story. Film sets during the 90's unrest Turkey.

title: Willie Nelson American Outlaw
description_full: Captures the most iconic moments from a one-night-only concert event honouring Willie Nelson and his music. This two-hour program is packed with over 20 original performances, never before seen interviews and captivating behind-the-scenes footage with Willie Nelson and some of music's biggest superstars.

title: Katherine Jenkins Christmas Spectacular
description_full: Classical music superstar Katherine Jenkins OBE returns to the iconic Royal Albert Hall, her all-time favourite venue, crafting a unique and unforgettable Christmas musical to play in cinemas worldwide from 1 December. Katherine Jenkins: Christmas Spectacular sees the Welsh sensation perform seasonal favourites and carols with full nostalgic Hollywood musical glamour and wonder. The production was given unprecedented and exclusive access to the historic venue which also marked the 50th time that Katherine has performed there. Katherine and friends, including beloved actors Vanessa Redgrave and Bill Nighy, Operatic icon Sir Bryn Terfyl, Italian Tenor Alberto Urso, American Broadway star Marisha Wallace, English National Ballet Lead Principal Erina Takahashi, the Royal Air Force Regiment Band and many more will bring joy and festive celebrations to audiences around the world this Christmas.

title: Shattered
description_full: The happily-married couple of Neil and Abby Randall have worked very hard to create a healthy and safe bubble for themselves and their only daughter, Sophie. However, their seemingly idyllic life will start crumbling into pieces when, out of the blue, the determined and methodical gunman, Tom Ryan, holds them captive, as his cold-blooded accomplice uses Sophie for leverage. Now, Abby and Neil have no other choice but to do Tom's bidding if they want to keep their child alive--and with every task they successfully perform--they see a piece of their orderly life being robbed from them. But, why is this perfect stranger bent on destroying three innocents?â€”Nick Riganas

title: My Rembrandt
description_full: This is set in the world of the Old Masters and offers a mosaic of gripping stories in which unrestrained passion for Rembrandt's paintings leads to dramatic developments and unexpected plot turns.

title: Up the Sandbox
description_full: A young wife and mother, bored with day-to-day life in New York City and neglected by her husband, slips into increasingly outrageous fantasies: her mother breaking into the apartment, an explorer's demonstration of tribal fertility music at a party causing strange transformations, and joining terrorists to plant explosives in the Statue of Liberty.â€”Anonymous

title: Woo
description_full: Darlene "Woo" Bates, played by Jada Pinkett Smith, has been dumped a little bit too many times, now this femme-fatale doesn't let just any man swing with her, and when she's set up on a blind-date with Tommy Davidson's character, it could be love.. if they don't kill each other first. "Woo" features cameos by Foxy Brown, LL Cool J, and Duane Martin.â€”Luis Montalvan

title: There's a Girl in My Soup
title_english: There's a Girl in My Soup
title_long: There's a Girl in My Soup (1970)
description_full: TV personality Robert Danvers, an exceedingly vain rotter, seduces young women daily, never staying long with one. He meets his match in 19-year-old American Marion, who is available but refuses any romantic illusions. Her candor and cynicism put him off at first, but after he sees her breaking up with her rocker boyfriend, he's attracted to her and invites her on an idyllic fortnight in France. She slowly pokes holes in his artifice and he comes to care for her. When they return to Londonwith the press thinking they're married, they come to a crossroads: go back to their old lives, marry each other, or invent a new, open relationship. Is Robert up to it?â€”

title: There Is a Light: Il padre d'Italia
title_english: There Is a Light: Il padre d'Italia
title_long: There Is a Light: Il padre d'Italia (2017)
description_full: Paolo and Mia, an introverted clerk and a unconventional pregnant woman, go on a journey looking for the father of Mia's unborn daughter.

title: The Karate Killers
description_full: U.N.C.L.E. agents Napoleon Solo and Illya Kuryakin travel around the globe in an effort to track down a secret formula that was divided into four parts and left by a dying scientist with his four daughters, all of whom live in different countries. Evil THRUSH agent Randolph also wants the formula, and is aided by his karate-chopping henchmen.â€”Marty McKee

title: Princess Cut
description_full:
Adapted from the award winning stage play, "Bitch Brow" by Demetra Kareman. Directed by award winning director Elaine Del Valle.
This genre bending suspense, dark comedy unites characters from opposite sides of the economic spectrum.
Set in "The Hamptons"-- a mostly blue color town, that between Memorial Day and Labor Day turns into the richest zip code in the United States.
One night post Labor Day--Teresa is a tough townie chick that works the overnight shift at the local Hamptons wash and fold laundromat. As she waits for her Uber driving FiancÃ©, Jimmy, to return Elodie, an uptight debutante, enters in need of a phone to call an Uber to return her to the city.
Teresa questions why a "fancy lady like" Elodie doesn't have a phone. Elodie's response, "Cancer, 5G waves...they say it's the equivalent of standing inside of a microwave."
Elodie offers Teresa cash for a ride and Teresa snags the cash and makes a phone call to Jimmy.
Meanwhile Jimmy unwittingly gets wrangled into a high stakes poker game with a bunch of frat boys at a waterfront mansion.
The women find common ground as they await Jimmy's return.
Teresa pours them a drink and Elodie pours out her woes explaining the pressures based on the expectations set upon her by her family and social status.
The two women find much in common, including their pending nuptials and the fact that they both chose princess cut engagement rings.
Elodie confesses to having failed the bar exam.
Teresa consoles Elodie, but soon realizes that not everything Elodie has said is true. Teresa confronts Elodie and before the end of the night one of the two women winds up dead.

title: Cry, the Beloved Country
description_full: South African church minister Steven Kumalo is summoned from his village to Johannesburg. There he finds that his son Absolom has been jailed in connection with a robbery in which a white man was killed. The father of the white man, James Jarvis, is a supporter of apartheid, the separation of the races which is the law of South Africa. When they encounter each other, both Kumalo and Jarvis come to unexpected realizations not only about their sons, but about the nature of their own humanity.â€”Jim Beaver

title: GarcÃ­a
description_full: Garcia (a 58-year-old factory watchman) has managed to accomplish his wedding promise to his wife, Amalia: buy her a house of their own. However, this wretched farm outside the city is far from his wife's dream. Garcia is ready to harvest the crops of so many years of hard work and stinginess but life has an unexpected turn as he arrives home from work and finds Amalia missing and no clue of his whereabouts. While trying to rescue her, Garcia bumps into Gomez (a run-down ex-cop) who will take him through a bizarre adventure that'll take him to unveil the secret behind Amalia's disappearance.â€”Federico Duran

title: A Monster in Paris
description_full: Paris, 1910. Emile, a shy movie projectionist, and Raoul, a colorful inventor, find themselves embarked on the hunt for a monster terrorizing citizens. They join forces with Lucille, the big-hearted star of the Rare Bird cabaret, an eccentric scientist and his irascible monkey to save the monster, who turns out to be an over-sized but harmless flea, from the city's ruthlessly ambitious police chief.â€”The Film Catalogue

title: The Chocolate Soldier
description_full: Maria and Karl Lang are the singing duo of Vienna. Maria is very flirtatious and Karl very jealous. Karl decides to masquerade as a Russian guardsman and attempts to make Maria flirt with him - to test her loyalty to him. As the Russian, Karl makes a vigorous attempt to seduce Maria. For a moment she accepts then rejects him. Karl is left in turmoil.â€”Kelly

title: The Amazing Dr. Clitterhouse
description_full: Dr. Clitterhouse is fascinated with the working of the criminal mind. His interest is so deep that he finds the best way to observe criminals in action is to become one himself. Whilst robbing a safe at an exclusive party he stumbles across an organized gang trying to do the same thing. He teams up with the gang to observe them in action but one of the members, Rocks Valentine would like nothing better than to see Clitterhouse out of the way.â€”Col Needham

title: Prime Risk
description_full: A female engineer, with the assistance of her pilot-wannabe male friend, discovers a way to rip off ATM machines, but in doing so stumbles upon a plot to destroy the U.S. monetary system.

title: American Women
description_full: Irish lads send an ad to the Miami Herald inviting fit and enticing women, between the ages of 20 and 21, to live in their isolated Donegal village. The whole town knows about the ad, and it sharpens everyone's sense of the opportunities for happiness already at hand. Kate, a publican with a young daughter, is separating from her husband and catches the eye of a bachelor sheep farmer. Kieran the butcher realizes that his assistant Siobhan is comely, and then he discovers she's fiery as well. Ollie sends off for Dutch skin magazines that the village postmistress won't release to him. The men, and women, find counsel in their movie-loving priest. Will anyone answer the ad?â€”

title: Sarafina!
description_full: As tensions of apartheid spread across South Africa, many students revolts to massive stone throw, a demonstration that comes in a wake of the introduction of Afrikaans language as a means of teaching. This sparks riots among school age young people who have resolved to do what it takes for freedom to come tomorrow. In a township of Soweto, a group of students, led by a beautiful and intelligent young girl, Sarafina, mastermind a plot to rise against the apartheid regime by vehemently rejecting the proposal to have Afrikaans as a medium of instruction. This angers the white people and results in a massive unrest of the students and those others supporting them. Meanwhile, Sarafina's mother accepts a job of a housekeeper in a white household and it angers Sarafina. Following the unrest of students and their possible torture and trial, Sarafina is released from prison, reunites with some of the colleagues and composes a "Freedom is Coming Tomorrow" song.â€”Isaac Museka Lupupa

title: Hold
description_full: "Hold" is a tense, spare, and lean drama about a young couple's relationship in the aftermath of a violent home invasion. Boasting no musical score and filmed in claustrophobic closeups, it investigates the frailty of the hero complex by putting a microscope on American paranoia.â€”Revision Films production staff

title: One of Our Spies Is Missing
title_english: One of Our Spies Is Missing
title_long: One of Our Spies Is Missing (1966)
description_full: Someone is using cats in experiments to develop a machine that can reverse the aging process, meanwhile a famous scientist (Dr Lancer) has gone missing, only for him to reappear looking 30 years younger. UNCLE agents Napoleon Solo and Illya Kuryakin are sent to investigate the plot in Europe - Illya is sent to London to discover who is abducting cats while Solo travels to Paris where Dr Lancer's daughter is working as a fashion model. They uncover a plot by female members of the fashion business to develop the anti-aging machine for their own use, however the suave THRUSH agent Jordin has other plans. Thus a race begins between UNCLE and THRUSH to take control of the machine.â€”Paul Hunter aka "Bob the Moo"

title: Luna
description_full: Grant and Christine are still struggling with the storm of grief following the death of their baby. They visit an old friend, Dean, with his new girlfriend Freya, in their isolated house by the sea. Dean tries but fails to control his drinking. Freya worries about the age difference between her and Dean. Christine confesses her secrets to Dean, upsetting his comfortably stable world of escapist fantasy and children's books. Over a long weekend, old loves, losses and resentments are revisited and the life of the dead child is lived out in a series of strange, hallucinatory dreams. Luna is a fantasy film about reality that uses cinematic imaginative language to portray the tangible and mundane alongside the fantastical and fleeting elements of life. The film combines live action with the unique animation and graphics of Dave McKean.â€”Anonymous

title: Deadlock
description_full: In a deserted mining town at the end of nowhere three desperate men fight over a suitcase full of cash.

title: Evil Alien Conquerors
description_full: My-ik [Diedrich Bader] and Du-ug [Chris Parnell] are evil alien conquerors from the planet Kabijj. They have exactly 822,000 tilkrons (2 and half days) to behead all of mankind. Otherwise they will feel the wrath of a 100 foot giant, named Croker [Tyler Labine]. Armed with only their swords, these inept evil aliens find Earth harder to conquer than planned. Will alcohol, fast food, mad cows, and women stand in their way? Or is the Earth doomed?â€”Daynera

title: Bad Girls Dormitory
description_full: During the night, Kitty (LYNNEA BENSON), a tormented dormitory girl, gets up and jumps off a window to her death, without an intervention from Nurse Stevens (REBECCA ROTHBAUM) and a Guard (MARK LEGAN).Paige (NATALIE O'CONNELL), a bosomy brunette with curly hair, lives with recurrent flash-back images of her rape by her father, Mr. Garfield (DAVID MLOTOK). She escapes home The girl marks down a newspaper ad calling for actresses for a "beneficent movie", walking through Times Square, New York, to a photo shoot. She passes a theater which has "Bubblegum Girls" and "Teen Strippers" up on the marquee. She felt the sleaze coming down at her from the casting office walls and the way Mr. Roland asked her to strip off her clothes. Next he calls Jack - a stud that was reading a magazine in his shorts in the next room - to do a scene with her, but they are interrupted by two Vice Cops (DICK BIEL and JONATHAN BUTNAM).Marina (TERESA FARLEY), a pretty Hispanic with an Afro-style hairdo, was with her Puerto Rican boyfriend Paco (JEFFREY IORIO; also combat scenes choreographer) when he is buying drugs from a couple of punks. The young man gives the alarm, and runs away, followed by Paco, who leaves the white powder in Marina's hands. Two Narcotic Agents (ALVIN HIPPOLYTE and BEN LIZZA) raid the derelict building and arrest the punk girl and Marina.Lori (CAREY ZURIS), has a sad face and blonde hair cut short, and is sentenced into detention because she committed murder. She had sex with her boyfriend Billy (SANDOR BLACK), in his car, only to see him get out and invite two friends - Ray (RYAN SEXTON), and Paul (SHAWN CARROLL) - to take her after he adjusted his trousers. First she tried to fight Ray off her, then she took a pistol from the glove compartment and shot Billy down, as he stood by the driver's door, watching her being screwed by his pal.The three girls eventually meet in the derelict New York Female Juvenile Reformatory. Don Beach (RICK GIANASI) is the concerned social assistant, apparently not as effective as he should be against a malevolent director, Miss Madison (MARITA). Before leaving the institution Doc goes unnoticed to the basement, where he first watches a girl sniffing drugs, and then Lori and five girls taking a shower in the nude.Lori is at the cafeteria when she's approached by the dark redhead queen-bee Lisa (JENNIFER DELORA) who loves to bitch, bully, and brawl, and her assistant, Rebel (DONNA ESKROW aka DONNA ESKRA), the archetypal white bad blonde. Lisa looks at Lori from head to toe, stares at her, and says, "You've pretty eyes."The juvenile girls in this detention dormitory come in all sizes and racial combinations, but all have in common the regulation uniform (sleeveless white T-shirts, blue jeans, and sneakers) and all look tough and mean, especially the trio of heavy, bull-dyke types: Dottie (KATE McCAMY), Deke (PARRI SHAHMANESCH) and Lenka (CATHRYN BISSELL).Some couples are formed at the cantina tables, out of love or friendship: Jen (JANE DONADIO), the small breasted curly virgin, arrested for prostitution with her pal Barb (FRANCES RAINES), with long and dark brown hair; Eula (RENATA COBBS), a beautiful black girl who cares for Gloria (SHERRY HOARD), a pregnant black girl.Rebel (DONNA ESKROW, or ESKRA), bumps into Marina (TERESA FARLEY)'s shoulder, and then throws abuse at her. The dark Latina snarls, "Don't make me get up. If I do, I'll be twisting some tits!" Of course Rebel dares her to, so Marina stands up from her table, and in a quick move wrenches Rebel's ear-ring off, tearing the left ear lobe in the process. The blonde screeches in pain, and punches the dark girl under the breasts. Cheered on by the other girls, they fall in a tangle and roll on the floor, then on top of a table, until they square up again, face to face, and Marina delivers a straight punch to the jaw that KO's the blonde.Paige strips for the drug addicted Doctor DeMarco (DAN BARCLAY), and entices him to have sex with her in the infirmary, while in a near-by cell Rebel does the same with Tom (MARC UMILE), one of the guards. Marina and a handsome black guard, Zulu (DAVID SOTOLONGO), also have passionate sex in the nude. The girls are using their bodies to get protection from the men, that will eventually prove necessary.Rebel is keeping a lesbian relationship with nurse Stevens (REBECCA ROTHBAUM), a slim woman, to get drugs from her, and with the queen-bee Lisa, whose toughness she admires.During visiting hours, Paco gives a small revolver to Marina, for her to hide in the dormitory, as part of a plan to assault the premises and rob the stocks of drugs stored in the infirmary.Valeska (CHARMAGNE ECKERT), a silver blonde, with lose hair to her waist, entices a guard (MARK LEGAN) into a dark corner, and gives him a blow-job (scene cut in some versions).Doctor DeMarco, under the effect of drugs, forces Jen to have sex with him, and the girl hangs herself afterwards. When the news is passed in secret to Barb at the factory yard, the girl has a hysterical fit, and her companions feel sorry for them.A party is organized by Miss Madison, attended by the girls and their boyfriends, including Paco and others - Roland (HARVE SOTO) and Jack (LANCE BRETT). Many of the girls end up dancing lasciviously to lyrics like "Innocent pearls can change to bad girls", but mostly the girls dance with each others. Some are taunting the male guards, to which Zulu is the first to respond, though he is stopped by the frozen stare of Miss Madison.McCoy (WILLIAM PETERSON), a mustachioed guard, pinches Lori's bum, and is slapped by her. Miss Madison is dumb enough to believe the man's false report, and sends Lori to the solitaire cell, with a brunette guard, Sperrazza (DEBRA LESTER). McCoy follows them, and when his female pal goes away, he enters the cell and rapes Lori, while Stevens watches them from a peep-hole, and climaxes with the scene. Afterwards, McCoy leaves, and Lori goes for a nude shower, despite there is a Big Guard (TOM BILLETT) using the facilities himself. He respects her, though. Stevens injects herself with more drugs.Queen-bee Lisa (JENNIFER DELORA), a curly dark brown hair inmate, defies Harper (RACHEL HANCOCK), a blonde guard of Amazonian proportions, with a large mane of curly blonde hair tied in a bun, to a one-on-one fight. No reason is given for the fight. The two women lock themselves in a basement warehouse, and exchange hard slaps, followed by body punches. They don't try to protect themselves, on the contrary, they hold each other close by a good grab on their hairs with the free hand, and they trade blows to the head, but most to breasts and belly, alternatively, except for a short grappling on the cement floor. When both are too exhausted to continue, they fall apart and agree to postpone the fight.Then Lisa goes in a killing spree. Angel-face Rebel entices Valeska to the basement under a false pretext, and Lisa strangles the silver blonde from behind with a piece of wire, cutting off her throat.Paige is forced by Miss Madison to meet with her father at a city restaurant. She starts talking with him, but soon the memory of what happened between them is too strong for her to keep quiet, and she starts denouncing his past actions in a loud voice, disturbing the customers, one of whom asks quickly for his bill (CHUCK MURDOCH), and leaves before the lunch is served, under the astonished stare of the Waiter (JOHN ABBATO) and the Counter Lady (MARIE LOFFREDO).Gloria has her baby in the basement, in secret, with the help of one of the guards - Tom - and her friends Eula, Marina and Paige. The baby (LOVELL DIXON) is going to be hidden before the escape attempt planned by Paco and his gang.Rebel calls Paige to the top of a staircase, where Lisa attacks her. Paige is so dizzy from the first blow to her head that she can't fight back, and is thrown down two flights of stairs, breaking her neck in the fall.Lori meets with the Big Guard, and lets him know the strange goings-on she has witnessed, and the fake suicides to mask Lisa's killings. They make love, to assuage her pains (off camera).The revolt erupts. First two, then a number of girls attack the female guards, and both the strong Sperraza and a small brunette (CAMILLE VALIDUM) go down without almost no fight.Harper goes after Rebel and Lisa, and they find themselves alone in the warehouse. Lisa defies Harper to fight to a finish, this time with the added spice of doing it in front of her lover, Rebel. Harper throws away her service truncheon, accepting a fair duel. It is a long, and brutal fight, in which the guard's advantage of size and weight prevail, exacting sadistic pain with repeated crotch kicks delivered by her heavy boots. Lisa is beaten senseless against a brick wall, under the stare of Rebel, who doesn't move until the butch guard walks away. (The character of Harper is not shown again in the film, creating the possibility that her death, eventually by a treacherous attack by Rebel, was cut before the movie's release.)Meanwhile, another triangle gets untangled in the basement. Paco has come to free his woman and battles with Zulu, both armed with heavy wooden stick and truncheon, respectively, under the eyes of Marina, who is holding Paco's gun. Zulu looks like he is going to be the winner, but Paco hits him in the crotch with his stick, the black guard is paralyzed with pain and falls to his knees, then he is clobbered senseless. Paco sadistically breaks Zulu's skull when he is defenseless on the ground, and when Paco goes to embrace and kiss Marina, she shoots him the belly.Tom is helping Gloria to escape with her baby, helped by Eula and Barb. Suddenly they found the escape route closed, and another guard stands between them and the route back. Barb is holding a shot-gun, and she shoots this guard, aiming at his crotch, thus opening way for their escape.Rebel first joins the revolt, then comes back to the basement, and helps Lisa to come back to her senses, and then they go upstairs together.Lori (CAREY ZURIS) gets a shotgun, kills McCoy and confronts Stevens, Madison and Lisa in the infirmary. Stevens is going to say that the one behind the drugs scheme inside the dormitory is the doctor, when he shoots her in the chest. Lori immediately fires at DeMarco, killing him, too.Madison goes forward, to grab Lori's arms, and Lisa suddenly picks up from under a bed a murderous looking primitive weapon, a big wooden club spiked with large nails. Lori is doubling over, trying to regain control of the heavy shot-gun, and Lisa strikes to her head. Lori is straightening up to face her, and shoots from below, at close range, taking her full in the chest and projecting her lifeless body back. Then she finishes blonde Miss Madison, again with a shot to her chest.The next scene, at the prison's cafeteria, creates a full circle. Rebel brings a New Girl (MAGGIE WAGNER), a pretty black haired girl, to Lori, who is sitting at the place where the late queen-bee used to sit. Lori looks the new girl from head to toe, stares her eye to eye, and says, "You've pretty eyes."

title: 1, 2, 3, All Eyes on Me
description_full: Ms. Leena, an art teacher for an 4th-grade elementary class, begins her lesson instructing her class to pair up and to begin to paint one another's portraits. This assignment creates a conflict between student's Anthony and Ricardo, as the former refuses to associate with his partner. The conflict escalates and Anthony is led outside of the classroom to have a discussion. While Ms. Leena is speaking with Anthony, a teenager is seen running towards a nearby classroom and spray-painting an 'X' on the classroom door, after which he hastily leaves. At this peculiar event, Ms. Leena ends her talk with Anthony, telling him to rejoin the class, and proceeds to call a co-worker to report the suspicious behavior. After her phone call ends, she grows even more concerned as she realizes her classroom door is also marked similarly, with a spray-painted 'X'.Ms. Leena rejoins the class and begins to clean the paint that was painted on Ricardo by fellow classmates. However, she is interrupted by the sound of blaring alarms. Locking the door, turning off the lights, and closing the curtains, the class goes into an urgent lock-down situation. While doing the best she can to keep her students quiet and pacified, Ms. Leena witnesses outside of her window two young teenagers putting on armored vests and distributing guns. The two gunman proceed towards doors with spray-painted 'X's, one being the most recently marked. Gun shots and screams are soon heard as Ms. Leena begins to barricade her own door. Realizing the safety of herself and her class is at increasing risk, she has her students move to a nearby classroom that a gunman has just left, though not before realizing one of her own students is missing.

title: All We Have
description_full: When Andres and Natalia met by accident, she wasn't impressed. In time they gravitated toward each other. But Paulo, a troubling figure from Natalia's past felt otherwise.
